WEBVTT

00:36.119 --> 00:38.539
[Rm]

01:03.605 --> 01:05.107
[Crowd chattering]

01:09.361 --> 01:11.441
Bob [over radio]:
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen.

01:11.572 --> 01:14.366
This is Bob Walker
speaking from Dallas love field...

01:14.533 --> 01:17.119
Where a large crowd has gathered
to await the appearance...

01:17.286 --> 01:20.247
Of president and Mrs.
John Fitzgerald Kennedy...

01:20.414 --> 01:23.792
Who have arrived from
carswell air force base in fort worth.

01:23.959 --> 01:26.920
Woman:
Lyndon, stop looking at that. Honestly.

01:28.338 --> 01:31.633
Mr. Vice president, we'll be in
the third car, the gray Lincoln.

01:32.843 --> 01:34.803
What's the word on yarborough?

01:34.970 --> 01:37.306
The president told the senator
he rides with you...

01:37.472 --> 01:39.808
Or he could walk
through downtown Dallas.

01:39.975 --> 01:43.478
Oh, isn't that sweet? Thank you, honey.

01:43.645 --> 01:46.023
Bob: Yes. Yes, it is the first lady.
Woman: Jackie!

01:46.940 --> 01:49.192
[Crowd cheering]

01:50.694 --> 01:53.572
The youthful Mrs. Kennedy
looking beautiful in her pillbox hat...

01:53.739 --> 01:56.408
And matching pink outfit.

01:58.535 --> 02:00.412
Mrs. Kennedy is followed
by the president...

02:00.579 --> 02:02.956
- Hello. You look lovely.
- Of the United States.

02:03.123 --> 02:04.291
Thank you so much.

02:04.458 --> 02:06.752
- Hi, Jackie.
- Hi, lady bird. It's good to see you.

02:06.918 --> 02:08.336
- Mr. President.
- Lyndon.

02:08.502 --> 02:10.422
- How are you?
- Good.

02:10.589 --> 02:12.424
Mrs. Johnson. Lovely as always.

02:12.591 --> 02:14.051
- Nellie: Lyndon.
- Hi, Nellie.

02:14.217 --> 02:17.471
Followed by Texas senator
Ralph yarborough.

02:17.638 --> 02:18.722
Good morning to you.

02:21.099 --> 02:22.899
Man:
This will be your vehicle, Mr. President.

02:23.060 --> 02:26.021
Bob: The crowd is jockeying
for a better look at the president.

02:26.772 --> 02:29.358
Wait, no. The president has
walked past the motorcade...

02:29.524 --> 02:32.778
And he's making his way
towards the crowd.

02:34.196 --> 02:36.490
-How are you? Jackie: Hello.

02:36.657 --> 02:39.159
- Shaking hands with people.
- John: Thanks for coming out.

02:39.326 --> 02:41.203
- Thank you.
- Some have cameras...

02:41.370 --> 02:44.289
To capture this historic moment.
Jackie: Thank you.

02:44.456 --> 02:47.042
- Thank you. Thank you very much.
- Real pleasure.

02:47.209 --> 02:50.879
They didn't expect to be shaking hands
with the president of the United States.

02:51.046 --> 02:55.425
This is quite a thrill for the people
who have waited here all morning.

02:55.592 --> 02:58.637
And once the motorcade departs,
it will head through the city...

02:58.804 --> 03:02.099
Where crowds are waiting for a view
of their president and his wife.

03:02.265 --> 03:04.385
- Lady bird: Thank you.
- Thousands will be on hand...

03:04.434 --> 03:07.813
For that motorcade, which
will move through downtown Dallas.

03:07.979 --> 03:10.816
Don't you just love Texas?

03:11.525 --> 03:14.027
Is there anywhere else you'd rather be?

03:15.904 --> 03:17.197
[Sighs]

03:21.535 --> 03:23.370
Walter:
This is regarding the farm bill

03:23.537 --> 03:26.123
we wanna vote in less than an hour.

03:26.289 --> 03:28.649
Get back to the leader.
Tell him people are still undecided.

03:28.792 --> 03:31.044
We wanna push this through
in the next half hour.

03:31.211 --> 03:34.423
Because I'm not general custer,
and this ain't little fucking bighorn.

03:34.589 --> 03:36.091
So if you have any objections...

03:36.258 --> 03:39.845
Tell me now before I head to the floor
of the United States senate.

03:40.011 --> 03:42.139
We got Cannon. Senator yarborough.

03:42.305 --> 03:44.725
- I'll be right with you.
- Juanita: Senator Mansfield, sir.

03:44.891 --> 03:48.270
- Mike. What's the number?
- About 48.

03:49.020 --> 03:51.732
"About 48" is not a number.

03:51.898 --> 03:53.817
Closest approximation I could get.

03:54.401 --> 03:57.821
Mike, I want you to imagine...

03:57.988 --> 04:01.366
Putting your little 2-inch pecker
on the edge of this table.

04:01.533 --> 04:03.994
Now, I grab a hatchet, and I tell you...

04:04.161 --> 04:07.831
That I'm gonna swing it down
about 2 inches from the edge.

04:07.998 --> 04:09.541
- Would you be nervous?
- Mm-hm.

04:09.708 --> 04:13.920
Well, that's how I feel when you tell me
that the count is "about 48."

04:14.087 --> 04:16.714
Now, what good is a whip
that doesn't know how to count?

04:16.882 --> 04:20.218
Go back out there
and get me an actual number!

04:20.385 --> 04:21.553
Juanita, dear?

04:21.720 --> 04:23.560
- Juanita: Yes, sir?
- Call dirksen's office...

04:23.597 --> 04:27.392
And tell him I'd like to speak
to the senator at his earliest convenience.

04:27.559 --> 04:30.771
- Yes, sir.
- George, get my tailor on the phone.

04:31.313 --> 04:32.731
Who is Mike Taylor?

04:32.898 --> 04:36.651
Who...? No, not "Mike Taylor." My tailor.

04:36.818 --> 04:40.447
The guy who makes my fucking clothes.
Get him on the phone now.

04:40.989 --> 04:42.574
- Senator yarborough.
- Mr. Leader...

04:42.741 --> 04:44.785
- I still don't take a drink.
- No?

04:44.951 --> 04:49.414
Now if you've called me in here to ask me
about my vote on the farm bill...

04:49.581 --> 04:53.001
I should tell you I have not changed
my position in the slightest.

04:53.168 --> 04:54.753
No problem. No problem at all.

04:55.629 --> 04:58.340
But, listen, while I got you here,
there is one question...

04:58.507 --> 05:00.550
I've been meaning to ask you.

05:00.717 --> 05:02.719
Have you got shit for brains?

05:03.553 --> 05:06.056
What the hell is your problem
with this farm bill?

05:06.223 --> 05:09.476
We should be doing a heck of a lot more
for the people who have less.

05:10.018 --> 05:14.981
The only thing more irritating
than a liberal is a liberal from Texas.

05:15.148 --> 05:16.388
[Whispers] The senator is here.

05:16.525 --> 05:19.277
- [Whispers] Bring him in.
- What my constituents want is...

05:19.444 --> 05:21.725
[In normal voice]
Your constituents are my constituents...

05:22.072 --> 05:26.076
And just because after three failed
attempts at the governor's mansion...

05:26.243 --> 05:28.829
You finally managed
to win an election...

05:28.995 --> 05:32.165
Hardly makes you an expert
on Texas voters.

05:32.332 --> 05:34.543
- Juanita: Sir?
- Don't tell me what they want.

05:34.709 --> 05:36.545
Senator dirksen is on the phone.

05:36.711 --> 05:38.380
I've got your tailor as well.

05:38.547 --> 05:42.175
You realize that juanita managed to get
the minority leader of the senate...

05:42.342 --> 05:45.554
Quicker than you could locate
a man who sews for a living?

05:45.720 --> 05:47.514
Hello, Everett, this is lyndon.

05:47.681 --> 05:52.352
We wanna bring this thing to the floor,
but can we do it without our two parties...

05:52.519 --> 05:56.398
Nipping at each other
like a pack of rabid dogs?

05:59.109 --> 06:02.863
Well, much appreciated,
as always, senator.

06:03.029 --> 06:04.197
-Juanita? Juanita: Yes, sir?

06:04.364 --> 06:06.449
Send dirksen a box of havanas.

06:06.616 --> 06:10.161
Walter, get ready to move on it.
You know, this could be your lucky day.

06:10.328 --> 06:13.039
You might be able to vote
your conscience on the farm bill.

06:13.206 --> 06:16.126
I like to think that is the only way
that I ever vote.

06:16.501 --> 06:18.920
Spoken like a true one-term senator.

06:19.796 --> 06:22.340
Means why haven't you
endorsed me for president?

06:22.883 --> 06:24.050
You haven't announced.

06:24.217 --> 06:25.468
Beside the point.

06:25.635 --> 06:28.430
- I like to hope that...
- You like Kennedy.

06:30.015 --> 06:33.393
Senator Kennedy and I,
we share many principles.

06:33.560 --> 06:37.314
You know, you got your show horses
and your workhorses.

06:37.480 --> 06:40.442
Now, Kennedy's a show horse:
Easy on the eyes...

06:40.609 --> 06:44.696
But when you need your field plowed,
he won't leave the barn.

06:44.863 --> 06:46.340
Ihearyou,
but what is most important...

06:46.364 --> 06:47.365
[Phone rings]

06:47.574 --> 06:49.075
- To me...
- Hold that thought.

06:49.242 --> 06:51.077
Hello there, this is lyndon Johnson.

06:51.244 --> 06:55.165
Now, you all made me
some real lightweight slacks...

06:55.332 --> 06:57.459
About three, four months ago.

06:57.626 --> 07:02.505
Kind of a light brown and light green.
Rather, soft green and soft brown.

07:02.672 --> 07:05.592
Like powder on a lady's...

07:05.967 --> 07:09.179
Face, and now,
I'm what they call "well-endowed"...

07:09.346 --> 07:11.723
So you give me
the average man's pants...

07:11.890 --> 07:16.895
I get all bunched up,
you know, like riding a wire fence.

07:17.062 --> 07:20.774
So give me another couple of inches
from where my nuts hang down...

07:20.941 --> 07:24.694
Round to the back of my bunghole.

07:24.861 --> 07:26.947
All right. Thank you very much.

07:28.490 --> 07:31.409
- You were saying?
- What is important to me...

07:31.576 --> 07:34.871
- Sir, that just put us over the top.
- Call for unanimous consent.

07:35.038 --> 07:37.082
Show horses, workhorses.

07:37.248 --> 07:39.125
You only get one.

07:39.292 --> 07:41.503
Go vote your conscience.

07:45.465 --> 07:47.217
[Rm]

07:47.425 --> 07:49.427
[People cheering]

07:54.099 --> 07:55.725
Nice of you to join us.

07:55.892 --> 07:59.604
Well, I heard there was a seat available.

08:00.897 --> 08:02.857
Bob: And as the motorcade makes
its departure...

08:03.024 --> 08:06.277
The presidential car is followed
by the secret service vehicle...

08:06.444 --> 08:09.739
Which is followed by vice president
and Mrs. Johnson.

08:11.700 --> 08:13.159
Oh. Heh.

08:13.326 --> 08:15.996
No, I'm... I'm perfectly fine.

08:16.705 --> 08:19.457
Guessing you Kennedys don't do
a lot of deer hunting.

08:19.624 --> 08:23.586
Well, when Kennedys fire weapons,
it's usually at Nazis.

08:23.753 --> 08:26.756
Lot of Nazis in hyannis port?

08:28.466 --> 08:30.719
We need to know if you're running.

08:31.386 --> 08:35.056
Quite comfortable in my post
as majority leader.

08:35.222 --> 08:37.851
Then perhaps you'd consider
endorsing my brother?

08:38.018 --> 08:41.312
I'll endorse whoever wins
our party's nomination.

08:41.479 --> 08:44.190
And there's no chance
that'll be you, correct?

08:44.357 --> 08:46.818
How many different ways
you want me to answer that?

08:46.985 --> 08:48.903
One would suffice.

08:49.279 --> 08:53.908
I have zero intention
of running for president.

08:55.160 --> 08:59.205
Johnson: I wanna know
why you're putting these signs up.

09:00.081 --> 09:05.628
For starters, Johnson has not said
that he's running for president.

09:06.379 --> 09:09.424
The reason I know is
because I'm fucking him!

09:11.301 --> 09:14.471
No, I'm not fucking him, I am him!

09:15.764 --> 09:18.244
Newscaster [on TV]:
His victory today was bolstered, in part...

09:18.391 --> 09:21.478
By the large catholic presence
in Wisconsin.

09:21.644 --> 09:24.856
- Up next, will be Illinois, New Jersey...
- What?

09:25.023 --> 09:27.025
Sir, I think it's time you announce.

09:27.192 --> 09:30.111
The next real test for Mr. Kennedy
will be in West Virginia...

09:30.278 --> 09:31.863
I haven't made up my mind yet.

09:32.030 --> 09:34.032
Connally:
Then tell me why I came all the way...

09:34.199 --> 09:36.910
From Texas to run a campaign
that doesn't have a candidate?

09:37.077 --> 09:40.371
Well, John, I imagine, to bask
in the pleasure of my company.

09:40.872 --> 09:44.125
Sir, I have been on the phone
all evening with delegates.

09:44.292 --> 09:47.796
Every one of whom is for Kennedy today
and would be yours tomorrow...

09:47.962 --> 09:51.800
- If you just announce you were running.
- A catholic won in a catholic state.

09:51.966 --> 09:55.220
Big fucking deal. You think
he could do that in West Virginia?

09:55.386 --> 09:59.265
This country is not gonna elect
a catholic president.

09:59.432 --> 10:01.351
He's starting to run away
from the pack.

10:01.518 --> 10:05.396
Nominations are not won
on the campaign trail.

10:05.563 --> 10:08.108
They are won on the convention floor.

10:13.696 --> 10:15.740
Bird, get me a drink, will you?

10:15.907 --> 10:17.617
Lady bird: All right.

10:18.785 --> 10:20.745
[Rm]

10:21.621 --> 10:23.873
He better decide if he wants this.

10:24.040 --> 10:26.501
He's never wanted anything more
in his whole life.

10:26.668 --> 10:28.461
- He'll run.
- It'd be too late.

10:28.628 --> 10:31.840
He's the best senate majority leader
this country's ever had.

10:32.006 --> 10:34.384
He works harder
than the other 99 senators combined.

10:34.551 --> 10:37.137
He doesn't understand
why he's not the party's favorite.

10:37.303 --> 10:39.931
He doesn't understand
why they don't just hand it to him.

10:40.098 --> 10:43.268
Nobody gets handed the presidency.

10:43.434 --> 10:45.520
Why won't he commit?

10:46.521 --> 10:48.940
- That's complicated.
- He's afraid.

10:49.107 --> 10:50.191
Of what?

10:50.358 --> 10:53.528
Hell, every politician's afraid
people won't vote for him.

10:53.695 --> 10:56.406
He's afraid people won't love him.

10:59.784 --> 11:01.984
Bob [over radio]:
All eyes are on West Virginia today...

11:02.120 --> 11:05.623
As voters cast their votes
in the state's primary election.

11:05.790 --> 11:06.916
In a surprising upset...

11:07.083 --> 11:10.295
Senator John Kennedy has won
the West Virginia primary.

11:11.045 --> 11:13.965
Many believed the issue
of his religion was insurmountable...

11:14.132 --> 11:17.177
But here is what senator Kennedy
had to say about it:

11:17.343 --> 11:20.180
I appreciate that question,
and I'll tell you when any man...

11:20.346 --> 11:24.517
Stands on the steps of the capitol and
takes the oath of office of president...

11:24.684 --> 11:28.897
He puts one hand on the Bible
and raises the other hand to god...

11:29.063 --> 11:32.442
As he takes his oath.
Now, if he... if he breaks his oath...

11:32.609 --> 11:36.738
I've never seen
a politician look that good on TV.

11:36.905 --> 11:38.948
Oh, angel, he's not that handsome.

11:39.115 --> 11:42.076
- I, John Fitzgerald Kennedy...
- Johnson: I've never seen a movie star...

11:42.243 --> 11:44.621
- Look that good on TV.
- Heh, heh.

11:45.163 --> 11:47.832
The office of president
of the United States...

11:47.999 --> 11:52.962
And will, to the best of my ability,
preserve, protect and defend...

11:53.129 --> 11:55.798
The constitution of the United States,
so help me, god.

11:55.965 --> 11:59.302
Jesus, he just swore himself in.

11:59.469 --> 12:01.389
Newscaster:
What's Jack got the rest haven't got?

12:01.554 --> 12:03.640
The "matinee" face?
The Kennedy name?

12:04.140 --> 12:05.183
The Kennedy fortune...

12:05.350 --> 12:06.601
[Television turns off]

12:07.644 --> 12:09.020
[Sighs]

12:10.396 --> 12:12.440
Lyndon, honey.

12:12.774 --> 12:14.651
Do you want this?

12:21.074 --> 12:22.492
[Rm]

12:22.784 --> 12:25.119
Do you know why I married you?

12:27.372 --> 12:30.959
I had other offers, but I chose you.

12:31.125 --> 12:34.712
- Do you know why?
- I have no earthly idea.

12:34.879 --> 12:35.922
[Clears throat]

12:36.798 --> 12:38.216
Because you asked.

12:39.717 --> 12:42.470
On our first date, when other boys...

12:42.637 --> 12:46.641
Would be thinking about
how to steal a kiss...

12:47.183 --> 12:49.811
You asked me to marry you.

12:51.479 --> 12:54.190
You didn't answer right away, though.

12:54.357 --> 12:55.733
Well, it hit me like a whammy.

12:55.900 --> 12:58.027
I'd only known you
for about 20 minutes.

12:59.362 --> 13:03.616
Ample time to fall in love with me.

13:06.119 --> 13:08.746
When father first met you, he said:

13:08.913 --> 13:14.002
"Daughter, you brought home
a lot of boys.

13:14.669 --> 13:17.630
This time, you brought home a man."

13:20.383 --> 13:23.344
At least he liked me right away.

13:24.220 --> 13:27.015
Angel, my point is...

13:27.515 --> 13:29.892
You knew what you wanted...

13:30.810 --> 13:32.687
And you got it.

13:33.938 --> 13:38.609
And I couldn't have said "yes"
if you hadn't asked.

13:52.874 --> 13:55.114
Newscaster [on TV]:
Convention fever grips Los Angeles...

13:55.251 --> 13:56.669
Where the democrats convene.

13:56.878 --> 13:59.922
Partisans of senator Kennedy radiate
the cheer and confidence...

14:00.089 --> 14:03.343
Of the powerful front-runner,
who is clearly the man to beat.

14:03.509 --> 14:06.512
The only major threat to Kennedy's hopes
among the declared candidates...

14:06.679 --> 14:09.140
Is senate majority leader
lyndon Johnson.

14:09.307 --> 14:14.103
Chairman: The convention of the
Democratic party of the United States...

14:14.270 --> 14:16.522
Is now called in session.

14:19.359 --> 14:21.444
Rowe: You need to go see
the Wyoming delegates.

14:21.611 --> 14:25.114
Why the hell are we still fighting
over western states?

14:25.281 --> 14:28.117
Their delegates are meeting
with Kennedy right now.

14:28.284 --> 14:30.078
Jack or Bobby?

14:30.244 --> 14:32.038
Teddy, sir.

14:32.205 --> 14:35.291
Christ, this place is infested.

14:47.303 --> 14:49.806
Bobby: "I have zero intention
of running for president"?

14:50.640 --> 14:53.935
I had a change of heart.

14:54.102 --> 14:56.687
Can't believe you'd look another man
in the eye and lie.

14:56.854 --> 14:59.494
Next one of you who says
a disparaging thing about Jack's health...

14:59.649 --> 15:01.359
I'll personally knock his teeth out.

15:01.526 --> 15:05.696
You said he's never felt better.
That wouldn't be a lie now, would it?

15:06.823 --> 15:08.908
Balloting starts in two hours.

15:09.075 --> 15:12.036
You don't take me down
in the first two rounds...

15:12.203 --> 15:15.039
- I'm gonna beat you.
- There won't be a second round.

15:15.206 --> 15:16.791
You seem awful confident.

15:16.958 --> 15:18.918
I can count.

15:20.461 --> 15:22.088
[Rm]

15:22.672 --> 15:29.303
Chairman: They will receive the call
of the roll of state, of voting...

15:29.470 --> 15:34.183
For the nomination of president
of the United States.

15:34.350 --> 15:37.520
Mr. Chairman,
Wyoming's vote will make...

15:37.687 --> 15:41.232
A majority for senator Kennedy.

15:41.983 --> 15:44.152
[Cheering on TV]

16:02.712 --> 16:05.047
Chairman:
Can we get the vote from Wyoming?

16:05.214 --> 16:09.635
First-round knockout, boys.
Just like rocky marciano.

16:09.802 --> 16:11.053
The times wants a comment.

16:11.220 --> 16:14.307
Tell them there's a new heavyweight
champion. His name is Kennedy.

16:14.474 --> 16:17.161
- How's the acceptance speech coming?
- Easiest speech I've ever had to write.

16:17.185 --> 16:20.730
Bobby, we're getting 20 calls a minute
about the vp. Everyone wants a name.

16:20.897 --> 16:22.732
First, we have to pick a name.

16:24.192 --> 16:26.319
[Telephone ringing]

16:33.618 --> 16:35.411
Hello?

16:38.247 --> 16:39.790
Lyndon.

16:40.458 --> 16:42.293
Lyndon, honey, wake up.

16:42.460 --> 16:44.420
- Wake up.
- What's the matter, bird?

16:44.587 --> 16:46.631
It's John Kennedy.

16:47.632 --> 16:49.425
[Rm]

16:50.551 --> 16:52.929
This is lyndon Johnson.

16:56.516 --> 17:00.686
Walter, order a fresh pot of coffee,
please. I have to get dressed.

17:00.853 --> 17:02.271
Yes, ma'am.

17:02.438 --> 17:07.234
Oh, yes. Yes, honey,
the red tie is so much better.

17:07.401 --> 17:09.487
Thanks, sweetheart.

17:10.238 --> 17:12.281
- Love... yeah, just fix it now a little.
- Yep.

17:12.823 --> 17:15.117
- Okay?
- Yep.

17:24.377 --> 17:25.836
[Knock on door]

17:31.259 --> 17:34.971
- Lyndon.
- Hi, Jack. Come on in.

17:35.471 --> 17:37.014
Thank you.

17:40.851 --> 17:44.146
Make sure symington, Humphrey
and Stevenson are all near their phones.

17:44.313 --> 17:46.524
We'll make our choice today.

17:46.691 --> 17:47.900
What's wrong?

17:48.067 --> 17:50.361
You're not gonna believe
where your brother is.

17:51.112 --> 17:55.283
Lyndon, you have more experience
and more talent, more wisdom.

17:55.449 --> 17:59.912
Unfortunately, this is politics,
and none of that matters.

18:00.329 --> 18:01.581
The better man won.

18:01.747 --> 18:03.165
I'm not better.

18:03.666 --> 18:05.376
Better-looking, maybe.

18:05.543 --> 18:06.544
[Chuckles]

18:06.711 --> 18:09.463
Yeah, if! Had some
of those Kennedy genes...

18:09.630 --> 18:12.258
