- How you getting along?
- John: Busy morning.

35:47.270 --> 35:50.649
How are we doing on this committee?

35:50.815 --> 35:51.941
Fine, Mr. President.

35:52.359 --> 35:55.153
Need to make sure
that this lockheed contract conforms...

35:55.320 --> 35:57.572
- To the committee's purpose.
- Well, ahem...

35:57.739 --> 36:00.158
Senator Russell has assured me that...

36:00.325 --> 36:04.120
We can expect to see
some significant changes in that plant.

36:04.537 --> 36:06.081
That's not what I hear.

36:07.415 --> 36:10.794
If you're concerned,
you should come to one of our meetings.

36:10.960 --> 36:13.213
If you'd like me
to express my dissatisfaction...

36:13.380 --> 36:16.257
In front of the entire committee,
that could be arranged.

36:16.424 --> 36:18.760
John: Lyndon, we're not awarding
a government contract...

36:18.927 --> 36:20.887
To a plant that violates civil rights.

36:21.054 --> 36:24.432
And you might remind senator Russell
that we don't need his help on this.

36:24.599 --> 36:27.560
We've got a lockheed plant
in California happy to build planes.

36:27.727 --> 36:31.356
With all due respect,
if you take that contract from Russell...

36:31.523 --> 36:34.109
All it will show is
that you can't make him do...

36:34.275 --> 36:36.444
One damn thing
that he doesn't wanna do.

36:37.737 --> 36:39.531
Now, you have to understand
his thinking.

36:39.698 --> 36:42.117
It's straight out of the last century.

36:42.283 --> 36:44.911
He's never gonna be
a progressive like us.

36:45.078 --> 36:46.621
[John chuckles]

36:48.289 --> 36:50.959
Why should we be working
with him on this, then?

36:51.126 --> 36:53.753
Because you don't wanna make
an enemy of Richard Russell.

36:53.920 --> 36:57.632
He'll put the brakes on every legislation
we're trying to move through congress.

36:57.799 --> 37:00.468
We're not gonna let
one senator hold us hostage.

37:00.635 --> 37:04.931
I suggest you don't wanna find out
how powerful that one senator can be.

37:05.098 --> 37:08.643
I need this committee to show
a strong record right from the start.

37:09.144 --> 37:12.355
Something that demonstrates
concrete changes on civil rights.

37:12.522 --> 37:16.276
We can't do that if we're giving
a huge contract to a discriminatory plant.

37:16.443 --> 37:19.154
On the contrary, I think we can, sir.

37:19.612 --> 37:23.241
If we send that contract to Georgia...

37:23.408 --> 37:27.829
Then I can get Russell to make
that plant hire a number of negros.

37:27.996 --> 37:30.957
And then, we can have
white men and black men...

37:31.124 --> 37:33.877
Working side by side
in the deep south...

37:34.043 --> 37:36.755
Building america's newest airplane.

37:36.921 --> 37:41.593
This can be one hell of a victory
for this administration.

37:48.308 --> 37:50.435
All right, lyndon, but...

37:50.894 --> 37:52.687
You're gonna have to move Russell.

37:53.688 --> 37:54.856
Thank you, Mr. President.

37:55.023 --> 37:59.444
Oh, and if! May, there'sjust
one other item I'd like to discuss.

37:59.611 --> 38:02.238
What's happening with Sarah Hughes?

38:02.405 --> 38:03.823
The judge from Dallas?

38:05.909 --> 38:09.204
You haven't responded
to my recommendation to nominate her.

38:09.370 --> 38:11.956
It's not your place
to make that recommendation.

38:12.123 --> 38:14.375
She'd make a damn fine judge.

38:14.542 --> 38:17.712
- She's too old.
- To you, everybody's too old.

38:18.129 --> 38:19.339
[John chuckles]

38:20.632 --> 38:22.967
Senators make those recommendations.
You know that.

38:23.134 --> 38:26.346
I promised Sarah Hughes
that appointment.

38:26.513 --> 38:28.932
It's Ralph yarborough's
recommendation to make.

38:30.099 --> 38:34.229
How's it gonna look to my state
if I can't get a federal judge appointed?

38:34.395 --> 38:38.191
I understand your frustration, lyndon,
but this is how it's gotta be done.

38:38.358 --> 38:41.986
We'll give Sarah Hughes a look
next time. Thanks for stopping by.

38:49.994 --> 38:52.455
Russell:
She'll be ready to take off this summer.

38:52.622 --> 38:54.499
Record time.

38:55.208 --> 38:57.418
Johnson:
Are you sure that big bitch will fly?

38:57.585 --> 39:00.672
Russell: She'll fly all right.
Built by Georgia's finest.

39:01.756 --> 39:03.508
Half of them, anyway.

39:04.551 --> 39:05.802
Thanks to you.

39:05.969 --> 39:07.595
[Chuckles]

39:10.390 --> 39:13.059
Jesus, lyndon.
God, put that thing away.

39:13.768 --> 39:15.812
Look at that.
Number-two man in Washington.

39:15.979 --> 39:18.189
Attorney generals
don't become president.

39:18.356 --> 39:22.694
There's a lot of things these Kennedy
boys do that no one else has done.

39:22.861 --> 39:24.904
He is a nice-looking boy.

39:30.159 --> 39:31.703
You know, I've been...

39:31.870 --> 39:35.290
Hearing disturbing news about
some goddamn civil rights bill.

39:37.750 --> 39:41.004
Yeah, I'm afraid
I've been hearing the same thing.

39:41.170 --> 39:43.732
I hope you're impressing on the president
the severity of the moment.

39:43.756 --> 39:48.136
Well, I have, but, unfortunately,
he doesn't answer to me or you.

39:50.513 --> 39:54.642
80 Kennedy won the presidency
by a fraction of a percent.

39:54.809 --> 39:57.562
Do you recall my margin of victory
that very same year? Ha-ha-ha.

39:58.104 --> 40:00.106
Mmm. Hang on, dick.

40:01.774 --> 40:05.445
- Yeah, I believe you were unopposed.
- That's right. I was. Unopposed.

40:05.612 --> 40:07.614
Six years before that too.

40:07.780 --> 40:10.283
And six years before that.
And you know what?

40:11.034 --> 40:14.454
Six years before that.
Are you plodding toward a point?

40:14.996 --> 40:19.542
I may not be president, but neither
am I ever in jeopardy of losing my job.

40:20.209 --> 40:23.046
So if the president sends
a civil rights bill to congress...

40:23.212 --> 40:27.050
It'll be my distinct pleasure
to see it die a painful death.

40:27.216 --> 40:29.552
And I'll kill every
other bill along the way.

40:29.719 --> 40:32.013
I don't care
if it costs my party the white house.

40:32.180 --> 40:36.684
I'm sure we can all sit down and come
to an agreement that we can all live with.

40:36.851 --> 40:40.396
It seems like every time we do that,
I'm the only one giving something up.

40:40.563 --> 40:43.441
And I'm about running out of things
that I can live without.

40:43.608 --> 40:48.112
Dick, you didn't have to give up
your billion-dollar airplane, did you?

40:48.905 --> 40:53.743
I'm not saying lay down and die,
but this train is leaving the station.

40:53.910 --> 40:57.538
So you can stand there
and watch it roll on by...

40:57.705 --> 41:01.793
Or you can hop on it with me
and try to slow the damn thing down.

41:10.510 --> 41:12.053
[Rm]

41:12.220 --> 41:13.888
[Sirens wailing]

41:16.808 --> 41:18.810
Guard: Move, move, move!

41:18.977 --> 41:20.019
Stay back! Stay back.

41:20.186 --> 41:22.386
Youngblood: We're not stopping
for anything, understand?

41:22.522 --> 41:24.962
- You bet, partner. You ready, bird?
- Youngblood: Here we go.

41:25.108 --> 41:26.901
- Let's move.
- Guard: Everybody back!

41:28.027 --> 41:29.445
Everyone back.

41:29.612 --> 41:30.780
Keep that area clear.

41:30.947 --> 41:33.032
Keep the area clear!

41:33.950 --> 41:35.618
Man 1: What's going on?
Man 2: Move!

41:36.411 --> 41:39.539
We're going right through
this door right here, sir. Here we go.

41:40.456 --> 41:41.499
Man 2: Copy that.

41:41.666 --> 41:43.126
Youngblood:
Get them out of here.

41:43.292 --> 41:45.503
- Back in the corner. Here we go.
- Woman: Sorry?

41:45.670 --> 41:46.713
Guard 1: Here you go.

41:47.296 --> 41:50.842
Nobody comes in unless he's got
a damn good reason to be here.

41:51.009 --> 41:53.886
- He wants you to call Washington.
- I'm not leaving this man.

41:54.053 --> 41:57.056
The president and governor connally
suffered gunshot wounds.

41:57.223 --> 42:00.309
I don't know the governor's condition,
but the president...

42:00.476 --> 42:01.644
It's bad.

42:02.478 --> 42:04.897
We need to get you to Washington
as soon as possible.

42:05.064 --> 42:06.482
I'm not leaving here.

42:07.108 --> 42:09.902
Mr. Vice president, safest place
for you is the white house.

42:10.069 --> 42:13.614
It would be unthinkable for me
to leave president Kennedy...

42:13.781 --> 42:16.242
While he fights for his life.

42:17.577 --> 42:19.037
Gentlemen...

42:19.203 --> 42:22.373
This is a time for prayer
if ever there was one.

42:31.007 --> 42:33.384
Newscaster [on TV]:
In another current trouble spot:

42:33.551 --> 42:35.136
Plaquemine, Louisiana.

42:35.303 --> 42:37.180
Mounted state troopers and police...

42:37.346 --> 42:40.099
Used tear gas
and high-pressure water hoses...

42:40.266 --> 42:43.561
In plaquemine last night to break up
a civil rights demonstration...

42:43.728 --> 42:45.897
That almost erupted into a race riot.

42:46.064 --> 42:50.026
How many more demonstrations do we
have to look at with hoses and dogs?

42:50.193 --> 42:52.737
I'm running out of ways
to explain to the press corps...

42:52.904 --> 42:54.590
Why the civil rights bill
isn't being sent to congress.

42:54.614 --> 42:56.574
I'm running out of ways
to explain it to congress.

42:56.616 --> 43:00.036
You take legislative action now,
all you'll do is fan the flames.

43:00.203 --> 43:01.871
We made promises
during the campaign.

43:02.038 --> 43:04.319
We sit on this bill,
our supporters will never forgive us.

43:04.373 --> 43:05.917
It is also the right thing to do.

43:06.084 --> 43:08.920
- It's the wrong time to do it.
- The wrong time?

43:09.087 --> 43:11.923
We've got kids in the street
getting their heads busted open.

43:12.090 --> 43:14.425
And how does sending
what will surely be...

43:14.592 --> 43:16.636
A failed bill to congress help kids?

43:16.803 --> 43:19.514
Well, burying our head in the sand
is not a solution.

43:19.680 --> 43:22.517
Neither is getting your ass handed
to you by Richard Russell.

43:22.683 --> 43:25.561
- I am so tired...
- Forget about the demise of the bill.

43:25.728 --> 43:27.772
What do you think
he'll do to your budget?

43:27.939 --> 43:30.441
Do you believe
they'll hold the budget bill hostage?

43:30.608 --> 43:33.236
To block civil rights,
they'll hold everything hostage.

43:33.402 --> 43:35.863
- To hell with Russell. We'll go around him.
- You can't.

43:36.030 --> 43:37.657
Then we'll go through him.

43:37.824 --> 43:41.702
We've got Martin Luther King writing
letters from jail. It's an embarrassment.

43:41.869 --> 43:44.997
- What are we waiting for?!
- Mr. President...

43:45.164 --> 43:47.458
I may not be the smartest man
in this room.

43:47.625 --> 43:51.587
Hell, I may not be as smart
as any man in this room.

43:51.754 --> 43:55.049
But I know the congress
of the United States.

43:55.216 --> 43:58.344
And if you submit
this civil rights bill now...

43:58.511 --> 44:00.429
It will never become law.

44:04.016 --> 44:05.059
Thank you, gentlemen.

44:17.780 --> 44:20.283
- What do you think?
- The time for negotiation is over.

44:20.449 --> 44:23.369
- What about southern democrats?
- You never had their support.

44:23.536 --> 44:26.080
This is one of those times
to draw a line in the sand.

44:26.247 --> 44:28.624
We could get to them through lyndon.
Send a message.

44:28.791 --> 44:31.294
They might listen to a southerner
who's on our side.

44:31.460 --> 44:33.713
What makes you think he's on our side?

44:34.839 --> 44:36.215
Kenny...

44:36.382 --> 44:38.384
Can we get this bill passed?

44:41.137 --> 44:43.097
I don't know, sir.

44:43.264 --> 44:45.433
It's not gonna be easy.

44:49.896 --> 44:53.232
Well, we don't do these things
because they're easy.

44:54.609 --> 44:56.110
We do them because they're hard.

44:58.863 --> 45:00.531
What do you want me to tell lyndon?

45:00.698 --> 45:02.742
He's no longer a part of this discussion.

45:03.326 --> 45:05.953
Russell: The Kennedys attended
private schools their entire lives.

45:06.120 --> 45:08.372
Now they wanna talk about equality.

45:08.539 --> 45:11.542
Voluntary integration is one thing,
but don't you think that I...

45:11.709 --> 45:14.837
As an American citizen,
shouldn't be forced to eat a hamburger...

45:15.004 --> 45:18.257
Next to someone in a restaurant
I don't wanna bump elbows with?

45:18.424 --> 45:21.052
Dick, I think it is unconscionable...

45:21.219 --> 45:24.722
That you, as an American citizen,
should ever...

45:24.889 --> 45:27.475
Be forced to eat a hamburger.

45:28.017 --> 45:29.477
Don't be a wisea... lyndon.

45:29.685 --> 45:30.686
[Chuckles]

45:30.895 --> 45:32.688
I don't find this topic amusing.

45:32.855 --> 45:35.274
Well, here's where I get confused.

45:35.441 --> 45:37.443
A baby calf is born.

45:37.610 --> 45:40.905
It grows into a cow,
lives on a farm, gets slaughtered...

45:41.072 --> 45:44.200
Butchered, packaged,
shipped, cooked...

45:44.367 --> 45:46.327
And finally served to you.

45:46.494 --> 45:51.374
Most, if not all, those steps required
the hands of black men.

45:51.540 --> 45:53.960
Why is it that
when it comes time to eat it...

45:54.126 --> 45:58.297
You can't stomach the notion of sitting
next to a black man while you chew?

45:58.464 --> 46:00.258
- If those...
- May I clear your plate?

46:00.424 --> 46:02.051
Oh, yes, Zephyr. Delicious.

46:02.218 --> 46:04.595
"If the law can compel me
to hire a negro...

46:04.762 --> 46:06.639
It can compel a negro
to work for me.

46:06.806 --> 46:09.934
And such a law would do nothing more
than enslave a minority."

46:10.393 --> 46:14.230
And that's what one senator had to say
about civil rights legislation. Thank you.

46:14.397 --> 46:17.566
That's probably strom thurmond.
He's an asshole and a moron.

46:17.733 --> 46:19.402
No, it was you.

46:20.820 --> 46:24.657
1949, your first speech
on the senate floor. Ha.

46:24.824 --> 46:29.078
You spoke for over an hour in opposition
to a civil rights bill just like this one.

46:29.912 --> 46:32.206
I remember watching you speak,
thinking to myself:

46:32.373 --> 46:34.333
"This young man's the future
of the south."

46:34.500 --> 46:35.960
[Johnson sighs]

46:37.211 --> 46:39.463
The best leaders of the time...

46:39.630 --> 46:43.509
From both our states,
voted for secession.

46:43.676 --> 46:48.055
And they were great men
who nearly destroyed america.

46:48.222 --> 46:51.267
I don't ever want a history book
to say that about me.

46:56.731 --> 46:58.733
Let me ask you something.

46:59.191 --> 47:01.551
[Whispering] When was the last time
you had a meal with her?

47:03.195 --> 47:05.281
[Whispering]
She's an employee...

47:05.448 --> 47:08.492
But if you think
that I would have any objection...

47:08.659 --> 47:11.579
Of breaking bread with her,
then you are a fool.

47:11.746 --> 47:13.622
So you're telling me she's your equal?

47:14.123 --> 47:18.169
That woman spends more time in
this house than anyone except lady bird.

47:18.336 --> 47:20.338
She is family.

47:20.504 --> 47:22.548
I don't know
how I missed the resemblance.

47:24.008 --> 47:26.927
Look, what I'm talking about here
is freedom.

47:27.386 --> 47:29.764
I'm talking about the preservation
of a way of life.

47:29.930 --> 47:33.517
A way of life
that you and I both grew up with.

47:33.684 --> 47:35.186
There's nothing wrong with that.

47:36.645 --> 47:39.106
Then why are we whispering?

47:40.358 --> 47:43.402
John [on TV]: One hundred years
of delay have passed...

47:43.569 --> 47:45.738
Since President Lincoln freed
the slaves.

47:46.113 --> 47:49.909
Yet their heirs, their grandsons,
are not fully free.

47:50.785 --> 47:54.288
They are not yet freed
from the bonds of injustice.

47:54.455 --> 47:57.666
They are not yet freed from social
and economic oppression.

47:58.167 --> 47:59.543
And this nation...

47:59.710 --> 48:03.089
For all its hopes and all its boasts...

48:03.255 --> 48:07.259
Will not be fully free
until all its citizens are free.

48:07.843 --> 48:11.097
Next week, / shall ask the congress
of the United States to act...

48:11.263 --> 48:14.308
To make a commitment
it has not fully made in this century...

48:14.475 --> 48:16.352
To the proposition that race...

48:16.519 --> 48:20.189
Has no place
in American life or law.

48:22.024 --> 48:26.320
Good morning, Mrs. Lincoln.
I'd like a moment with the president.

48:28.823 --> 48:32.660
Sir, vice president Johnson is here.
What shall I tell him?

48:33.661 --> 48:35.287
You can go in.

48:35.454 --> 48:37.081
Thank you.

48:45.381 --> 48:46.799
Good morning, Mr. President.

48:46.966 --> 48:49.927
- How you getting along?
- You're up early, lyndon.

48:51.345 --> 48:55.307
No, the president hasn't arrived yet,
but what do you need?

48:58.436 --> 49:00.396
It can wait.

49:00.938 --> 49:02.565
What's on your mind?

49:05.943 --> 49:11.031
I wanna know
the president's intentions for '64.

49:11.490 --> 49:14.952
Does he wanna keep me on the ticket?

49:16.120 --> 49:19.206
Dropping you from the ticket
would be more trouble than it's worth.

49:19.373 --> 49:21.500
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I was on my way.

49:22.334 --> 49:23.377
Bobby.

49:28.424 --> 49:30.134
Why don't you like me?

49:31.469 --> 49:32.845
Your brother likes me.

49:33.012 --> 49:34.680
Your father likes me.

49:34.847 --> 49:37.224
What is it makes you hate me so much?

49:38.142 --> 49:40.978
I don't hate you. I just... I...

49:41.145 --> 49:43.063
We see the world in very different ways.

49:44.857 --> 49:46.817
Then why do you keep me around?

49:46.984 --> 49:49.361
I was in congress 24 years...

49:49.528 --> 49:53.365
But you never asked for my help
in legislative issues.

49:53.532 --> 49:55.159
I'm from the south...

49:55.326 --> 49:58.746
But when you need help down there,
you go to other southerners.

49:58.913 --> 50:01.332
Why don't you just...

50:01.499 --> 50:03.083
Put me out to pasture?

50:03.250 --> 50:07.922
You've worked overtime
making sure I'm politically through.

50:08.088 --> 50:11.509
I can never run for elected office again.

50:11.675 --> 50:16.639
Hell, I don't even know
if I can help the president out in '64.

50:23.604 --> 50:26.690
This isn't about '64, is it?

50:27.441 --> 50:28.984
[Nt]

50:29.235 --> 50:31.403
It's about '68.

50:32.363 --> 50:36.659
You don't wanna bring in someone new.
You keep me here precisely because...

50:36.825 --> 50:40.538
You've made me politically irrelevant.

50:41.622 --> 50:44.250
That way, in '68...

50:47.586 --> 50:51.465
The vice president isn't
the presumptive nominee.

50:51.632 --> 50:53.425
You are.

50:55.219 --> 50:57.263
You think I'd be that calculating?

50:58.138 --> 51:00.266
I know I would be.

51:00.474 --> 51:02.476
[Nt]

51:26.458 --> 51:30.212
If either of you get a betterjob offer,
I suggest you take it.

51:30.379 --> 51:33.048
My future is behind me.

51:37.761 --> 51:40.139
[Nt]

51:56.280 --> 51:57.656
He's gone.

52:19.470 --> 52:21.138
Mr. President?

52:42.868 --> 52:46.330
Sir, I need to announce
the death of president Kennedy.

52:47.956 --> 52:50.834
Ahem. I want you to hold off
on that, Malcolm.

52:51.001 --> 52:54.588
Rufus, get some cars set up and let
the drivers know we're ready to move.

52:54.755 --> 52:58.717
Emery, have your people
locate luci and Lynda bird.

52:58.884 --> 53:01.762
I want my daughters to meet us
when we arrive in Washington.

53:01.929 --> 53:06.517
Also, have McNamara, rusk and the rest
of the cabinet on the ground at Andrews.

53:06.684 --> 53:09.019
Rusk and five cabinet members
are on a plane to Japan.

53:09.186 --> 53:11.188
Turn it around.

53:11.355 --> 53:14.024
I need you to tell Mrs. Kennedy
it's time to go.

53:14.191 --> 53:15.901
Mrs. Kennedy won't leave
without the body.

53:16.068 --> 53:18.612
Well, we won't leave here
without Mrs. Kennedy.

53:18.779 --> 53:21.824
- Sir, we need to get you in the air.
- Not without Jackie.

53:21.990 --> 53:24.702
- Then let's wait for her at the plane.
- Fine.

53:24.868 --> 53:27.287
Cliff, I need people I know close by.

53:28.122 --> 53:30.874
Congressmen, I want you
flying back to Washington with me.

53:31.041 --> 53:32.751
-Yes, sir. Kilduff: Sir...

53:32.918 --> 53:36.588
The American people need to know
that president Kennedy has died.

53:39.800 --> 53:42.052
On April 14th, 1865...

53:42.219 --> 53:45.472
Two men attempted to kill
secretary of state William seward...

53:45.639 --> 53:47.725
Stabbing him in his home.

53:47.891 --> 53:50.269
At the same time,
another assassin was on his way...

53:50.436 --> 53:53.647
To take the life
of vice president Andrew Johnson.

53:53.814 --> 53:55.899
This was the same night...

53:56.066 --> 53:58.485
That John wilkes booth
shot Abraham Lincoln.

53:58.652 --> 54:03.824
We don't know the extent
of this conspiracy or who's behind it.

54:03.991 --> 54:06.702
Malcolm, you're to announce
president Kennedy's death...

54:06.869 --> 54:09.705
Only after the rest of us
are safely on board that plane.

54:09.872 --> 54:12.291
Otherwise, you're gonna make
these boys' jobs...

54:12.458 --> 54:14.626
A whole hell of a lot harder.
Youngblood: Sir.

54:21.008 --> 54:23.844
[Chattering indistinctly]

54:33.896 --> 54:36.148
It was only on October the 24th...

54:36.315 --> 54:39.526
That our ambassador
to the United Nations, adlai Stevenson...

54:39.693 --> 54:43.697
Was assaulted in Dallas,
leaving a dinner meeting there.

54:46.366 --> 54:49.828
From Dallas, Texas,
the flash, apparently official...

54:49.995 --> 54:55.000
President Kennedy died
at 1 pm. Central standard time...

54:55.667 --> 54:58.754
2 o'clock eastern standard time...

54:58.921 --> 55:01.507
Some 38 minutes ago.

55:03.133 --> 55:04.927
[Nt]

55:06.136 --> 55:10.265
Vice president lyndon Johnson
has left the hospital in Dallas...

55:10.432 --> 55:14.019
But we do not know
to where he has proceeded.

55:14.186 --> 55:17.856
Presumably, he will be taking
the oath of office shortly...

55:18.023 --> 55:23.195
And become the 36th president
of the United States.

55:23.695 --> 55:26.406
Johnson: I wanna thank everybody
for getting here so quickly.

55:26.573 --> 55:30.786
And I'm gonna need your help
back in Washington.

55:30.953 --> 55:33.497
- Marie, can you join me in the next room?
- Yes, sir.

55:33.664 --> 55:35.165
- Excuse me.
- At Dallas airport...

55:35.332 --> 55:38.335
Was cheerful, waving...

55:41.505 --> 55:43.382
[Nt]

56:02.192 --> 56:04.361
This is lyndon Johnson.

56:06.738 --> 56:09.074
I need you to take notes.

56:10.492 --> 56:12.953
Guthman: Sir, I got lyndon Johnson
on the phone.

56:18.959 --> 56:20.002
Hello, lyndon.

56:21.128 --> 56:23.422
Bobby, I am...

56:23.589 --> 56:26.300
So sorry for your loss.

56:26.967 --> 56:28.635
Words cannot express...

56:28.802 --> 56:31.263
The whole country mourns with you.

56:32.306 --> 56:34.558
- Thank you.
- Listen, Bobby...

56:34.725 --> 56:37.728
I need your opinion about something.

56:37.895 --> 56:40.522
People down here are saying that I...

56:40.689 --> 56:44.359
I should take the oath of office
as soon as possible...

56:44.776 --> 56:46.695
Before we depart.

56:46.862 --> 56:49.114
What do you think about that?

56:50.282 --> 56:52.784
Well, I think it would be nice
for president Kennedy...

56:52.951 --> 56:54.912
To return to Washington as president.

56:55.746 --> 56:59.416
Well, I understand that. I do.

56:59.583 --> 57:03.337
But we got confusion down here,
and it's liable to turn into panic.

57:03.503 --> 57:06.673
I think it would put
a lot of people at ease...

57:06.840 --> 57:11.553
If I was to take the oath right now.

57:12.638 --> 57:14.973
What's the matter?
You afraid you'll arrive...

57:15.140 --> 57:17.059
And the white house won't be here?

57:17.893 --> 57:20.604
I think it's important
that the world knows...

57:20.771 --> 57:25.359
That the American government is
functioning and someone's in charge.

57:25.525 --> 57:27.611
Well, I don't know what the hurry is...

57:27.778 --> 57:30.739
But if you're so insistent
on taking the oath, take the oath.

57:31.198 --> 57:34.201
Okay, Bobby, then I'll take the oath.

57:34.368 --> 57:35.410
Fine, lyndon.

57:35.577 --> 57:38.205
Now, we have
to be absolutely certain that...

57:38.372 --> 57:39.748
We do this the right way.

57:39.915 --> 57:43.168
So I need you to get me
the precise wording.

57:43.669 --> 57:46.880
- Is that all?
- One last thing.

57:47.047 --> 57:48.757
Who do we need to administer it?

57:49.174 --> 57:50.425
Any judge can do it.

57:50.842 --> 57:52.719
Okay, well, thank you, Bobby.

57:52.886 --> 57:54.596
God bless.

57:55.973 --> 57:57.391
Get me Sarah Hughes.

57:58.183 --> 57:59.893
I do solemnly swear...

58:00.060 --> 58:01.395
I do solemnly swear...

58:01.561 --> 58:03.605
That I will faithfully execute...

58:03.772 --> 58:05.983
That I will faithfully execute...

58:06.149 --> 58:08.443
The office of president
of the United States...

58:08.944 --> 58:11.363
The office of president
of the United States...

58:11.530 --> 58:14.574
And will, to the best of my ability...

58:14.741 --> 58:17.411
And will, to the best of my ability...

58:17.577 --> 58:20.038
- Preserve, protect...
- Preserve, protect...

58:20.205 --> 58:22.082
- And defend...
- And defend...

58:22.249 --> 58:25.210
The constitution of the United States.

58:25.377 --> 58:28.922
- The constitution of the United States.
- 80 help me god.

58:29.965 --> 58:32.009
80 help me god.

58:33.468 --> 58:34.928
[Rm]

58:35.178 --> 58:38.724
Newscaster [on radio]: At 3:39 pm,
the machinery of our government...

58:38.890 --> 58:41.977
Conferred the unique powers
and awesome responsibilities...

58:42.144 --> 58:45.689
Of the presidency
upon lyndon baines Johnson.

58:45.856 --> 58:50.235
There is, in the urgent necessity
of this continuity of presidential power...

58:50.402 --> 58:53.030
A reassurance
that the government will function...

58:53.196 --> 58:56.783
The nation endure,
no matter how great the tragedy...

58:56.950 --> 58:58.869
No matter how grievous the shock.

58:59.036 --> 59:00.412
Welcome back, sir.

59:00.579 --> 59:02.998
- Mrs. Johnson.
- Glad you're safe, sir.

59:03.165 --> 59:06.293
Early reports said you'd been shot
or that you'd had a heart attack.

59:06.460 --> 59:09.046
Agent youngblood
took excellent care of us.

59:09.212 --> 59:10.255
- Bird?
- Yes?

59:10.422 --> 59:14.176
Can you get your good stationery? I'd like
to write letters to Caroline and John.

59:14.342 --> 59:15.635
- Juanita.
- Yes, sir?

59:15.802 --> 59:18.638
- Come with me. I need to make calls.
- Yes, sir.

59:19.139 --> 59:22.934
Yes, it has been a shocking day.

59:23.977 --> 59:25.979
Well, I...

59:26.938 --> 59:29.900
You know,
I feel inadequate to the task.

59:30.067 --> 59:33.987
And I'm gonna be relying
on your good, sound judgment.

59:34.154 --> 59:35.655
And...

59:36.490 --> 59:37.657
[Sighs]

59:38.241 --> 59:39.326
[Clears throat]

59:39.493 --> 59:41.703
I'll be calling on you...

59:41.870 --> 59:44.206
To get your advice.

59:44.372 --> 59:48.251
You know how much
I've admired you over the years.

59:48.710 --> 59:52.255
Well, please give my love
to Mrs. Eisenhower.

59:52.422 --> 59:53.507
No, no, no.

59:53.673 --> 59:57.052
Anything Harry Truman has to say,
I'm all ears.

59:57.219 --> 59:59.846
I'm gonna be calling on you real soon.

01:00:00.013 --> 01:00:03.350
J. Edgar, you are not just
the head of the federal bureau...

01:00:03.517 --> 01:00:05.852
You're as close
as "close" can be to me.

01:00:06.019 --> 01:00:10.524
Now, let's just try to put
our country at close ranks...

01:00:10.690 --> 01:00:15.445
And pull ourselves out of this
terrible situation we find ourselves in.

01:00:15.612 --> 01:00:18.990
Nellie, how's our boy?
Is he in a lot of pain?

01:00:19.449 --> 01:00:21.243
Well, tell John I'm praying for him...

01:00:21.409 --> 01:00:25.247
And bird and I are sending you both
a big hug and a kiss.

01:00:25.413 --> 01:00:28.333
Pierre, it makes no sense
to be jumping ship now...

01:00:28.500 --> 01:00:30.544
When we're all
on the same fucking ocean.

01:00:30.710 --> 01:00:32.462
[Whispers]
I'm going to bed, dear.

01:00:32.629 --> 01:00:33.922
Okay, baby.

01:00:34.089 --> 01:00:37.300
Now, I need you now
more than he ever did.

01:00:38.009 --> 01:00:41.721
Johnson: Lady bird and I will remain
at the elms for the foreseeable future.

01:00:41.888 --> 01:00:44.850
And Jackie can stay at the white house
for as long as she likes.

01:00:45.016 --> 01:00:48.645
George: Bundy said you and your staff
should move to the oval office tomorrow.

01:00:48.812 --> 01:00:50.272
Johnson: Fine.

01:00:50.438 --> 01:00:52.149
Ted sorensen?

01:00:52.315 --> 01:00:53.942
It's lyndon Johnson.

01:00:54.943 --> 01:00:56.361
Hello, Mr. President.

01:00:56.528 --> 01:00:58.029
I'm glad I tracked you down.

01:00:58.196 --> 01:01:01.241
Sir, senator Russell's
pulled up to the house.

01:01:02.909 --> 01:01:06.413
Listen, I know how much
you loved president Kennedy.

01:01:07.164 --> 01:01:08.540
And he loved you too.

01:01:08.707 --> 01:01:11.543
You were a trusted servant,
loyal to the end.

01:01:13.003 --> 01:01:16.840
Ted, I need you now
more than he ever did.

01:01:17.007 --> 01:01:19.217
How many senators
did Russell bring with him?

01:01:19.384 --> 01:01:21.428
Looks like the entire southern delegation.

01:01:21.595 --> 01:01:23.013
Any idea what they want?

01:01:23.180 --> 01:01:25.682
Russell said they just wanted
to wish you well.

01:01:25.849 --> 01:01:28.977
No. They could've done that
over the phone.

01:01:30.437 --> 01:01:32.022
[Applause]

01:01:37.944 --> 01:01:39.946
Mr. President.

01:01:42.532 --> 01:01:44.201
Mr. President.

01:01:45.035 --> 01:01:47.162
In this dark hour
of our nation's history...

01:01:47.329 --> 01:01:49.915
We must remember
to give thanks for our blessings.

01:01:51.291 --> 01:01:56.296
Because out of the despicable ashes
of a presidential assassination...

01:01:58.798 --> 01:02:01.468
A new leader has emerged.

01:02:01.635 --> 01:02:04.679
And we're all here to offer our support.

01:02:04.846 --> 01:02:06.181
Man: Yes, sir.

01:02:06.348 --> 01:02:11.061
After a century of persecution,
a century of being treated as inferior...

01:02:11.228 --> 01:02:14.022
After 100 long years...

01:02:14.189 --> 01:02:16.733
We finally have one of our own
leading this nation.

01:02:18.360 --> 01:02:21.321
America has a southern president.

01:02:22.739 --> 01:02:25.951
And we could think
of no finer representative for our people.

01:02:28.745 --> 01:02:29.871
Dear lord...

01:02:31.248 --> 01:02:34.334
Continue to watch over our president...

01:02:34.501 --> 01:02:37.545
And fill him with the strength...

01:02:37.712 --> 01:02:41.841
And wisdom as he works to do
the same for all your children.

01:02:42.676 --> 01:02:44.427
-Amen. All: Amen.

01:02:47.138 --> 01:02:48.932
Thank you, dick. Gentlemen.

01:02:55.689 --> 01:02:57.107
Johnson:
Good morning, gentlemen.

01:02:57.274 --> 01:02:58.876
O'brien: Mr. President.
O'Donnell: Mr. President.

01:02:58.900 --> 01:03:01.403
I'm pleased to see you
back at work already.

01:03:02.028 --> 01:03:05.615
The constitution put me
in the white house...

01:03:05.782 --> 01:03:10.078
But there's no law
to make you stay here with me.

01:03:11.746 --> 01:03:15.625
Now, I know you loved
president Kennedy...

01:03:15.792 --> 01:03:19.629
But I need you now
more than he ever did.

01:03:20.380 --> 01:03:23.258
Not that I loved Caesar less...

01:03:23.425 --> 01:03:26.094
But that I loved Rome more.

01:03:32.600 --> 01:03:36.187
- I can't believe he quoted Shakespeare.
- Can't believe he quoted brutus.

01:03:36.980 --> 01:03:38.523
Johnson:
Good morning, Mrs. Lincoln.

01:03:38.898 --> 01:03:40.608
Good morning.

01:03:41.735 --> 01:03:44.237
Now, I have an 11:30 appointment.

01:03:44.404 --> 01:03:46.781
Can I get my girls
in the office by then?

01:03:48.158 --> 01:03:50.076
I'll do the best I can.

01:03:52.412 --> 01:03:54.414
I know you will.

01:04:13.683 --> 01:04:16.144
Walter: Mrs. Kennedy
had the new carpet installed...

01:04:16.311 --> 01:04:17.645
When everybody went to Texas.

01:04:19.481 --> 01:04:22.108
Oh. Strange choice.

01:04:25.570 --> 01:04:27.489
What's going on?

01:04:28.823 --> 01:04:29.949
[Clears throat]

01:04:30.617 --> 01:04:35.705
Mr. Johnson told me
to clear everything out immediately.

01:04:40.502 --> 01:04:42.837
You don't waste any time,
do you, lyndon?

01:04:43.004 --> 01:04:45.423
- Excuse me?
- It's going to take some doing to get...

01:04:45.590 --> 01:04:48.885
All of president Kennedy's
belongings packed and relocated.

01:04:49.511 --> 01:04:51.638
I was told to use this office.

01:04:51.805 --> 01:04:54.641
Just like you were told
to take the oath in Dallas?

01:04:56.309 --> 01:04:57.727
[Whispering] Bobby...

01:04:57.894 --> 01:05:00.230
I'm not trying
to shove myself anywhere.

01:05:00.397 --> 01:05:04.484
In fact, I told Jackie she could stay
in the east wing as long as she needs.

01:05:04.651 --> 01:05:08.530
Well, that's not really the part of the
building that you're interested in, is it?

01:05:09.114 --> 01:05:11.574
I'm just trying to do my job.

01:05:11.991 --> 01:05:16.162
My brother's coffin is down the hall.
This is not where our attention should be.

01:05:20.667 --> 01:05:23.962
We all mourn for your brother.

01:05:24.129 --> 01:05:27.590
But somebody has to tend
to the business of the country.

01:05:27.757 --> 01:05:30.677
Mourning for my brother is
the business of the country.

01:05:33.346 --> 01:05:35.765
We can come back later
after my cabinet meeting.

01:05:36.391 --> 01:05:38.226
Your cabinet...

01:05:45.942 --> 01:05:47.527
Bobby...

01:05:47.694 --> 01:05:49.863
I know you've got a lot on your mind.

01:05:51.030 --> 01:05:54.117
But I want you to stand with me
as Attorney General.

01:05:54.617 --> 01:05:58.121
You've already got one photograph
with a grieving Kennedy at your side.

01:05:58.288 --> 01:05:59.706
Do you really need another?

01:06:00.999 --> 01:06:03.084
[Rm]

01:06:04.544 --> 01:06:07.213
I'd appreciate it if you kept me
apprised of any...

01:06:07.380 --> 01:06:09.007
Change in plans you might have.

01:06:09.174 --> 01:06:10.675
Okay.

01:06:10.842 --> 01:06:12.594
Yeah, I know where to find you.

01:06:18.183 --> 01:06:20.185
[Rm]

01:06:28.359 --> 01:06:32.822
Cronkite: People gathered outside
the grounds of the white house today...

01:06:32.989 --> 01:06:36.367
Watching the dignitaries
and government officials...

01:06:36.534 --> 01:06:38.703
And representatives
of foreign governments...

01:06:38.870 --> 01:06:41.998
Come through the gates
and go to pay last respects...

01:06:42.165 --> 01:06:46.044
To president Kennedy, lying in
the east room of the white house.

01:06:46.211 --> 01:06:50.298
Our reporter, David schumacher,
was outside the white house...

01:06:50.465 --> 01:06:54.177
And talked to some of those people.
Let's look at that film now.

01:06:54.344 --> 01:06:59.390
Just word... just... I just can't describe
just how I feel at this time.

01:06:59.557 --> 01:07:00.975
It just seems empty.

01:07:01.142 --> 01:07:05.522
It just doesn't seem like anybody else
could fill the place the way he did.

01:07:05.897 --> 01:07:08.149
Sir, we need to discuss
your address to congress.

01:07:08.316 --> 01:07:10.401
Man: It's unreal.
This can't happen in our country.

01:07:10.568 --> 01:07:13.071
Woman:
I feel the profound grief that...

01:07:13.238 --> 01:07:15.740
I'm not ready for that yet.

01:07:16.866 --> 01:07:19.536
Walter: Well, with all due respect,
you better get ready.

01:07:19.702 --> 01:07:22.205
President Kennedy's burial
has been set for Monday.

01:07:22.372 --> 01:07:25.041
Thursday being Thanksgiving,
we don't have much of a window.

01:07:25.208 --> 01:07:29.837
Thinking that, possibly,
the only thing we could do is to...

01:07:30.004 --> 01:07:33.800
Pray that lyndon Johnson
can carry on.

01:07:35.885 --> 01:07:39.013
Johnson gave Pierre the "I need
you more than he needed you" speech.

01:07:39.180 --> 01:07:40.223
What did you tell him?

01:07:40.390 --> 01:07:43.351
Salinger: I told him I'd stay as press
secretary as long as he needed me.

01:07:43.851 --> 01:07:44.936
Till Tuesday.

01:07:45.103 --> 01:07:46.312
[All laugh]

01:07:46.479 --> 01:07:49.774
Johnson's not gonna be satisfied till
every one of us promises to serve him.

01:07:49.941 --> 01:07:51.526
So, what are we doing here?

01:07:52.777 --> 01:07:54.862
Schlesinger:
In his inaugural address...

01:07:55.029 --> 01:07:56.990
President Kennedy declared that...

01:07:57.156 --> 01:08:01.119
The torch had been passed
to a new generation ofamericans.

01:08:01.286 --> 01:08:03.538
The question before us now is:

01:08:03.705 --> 01:08:05.832
Who should be the custodian
of that torch?

01:08:06.040 --> 01:08:07.083
[Rm]

01:08:07.250 --> 01:08:09.836
The constitution may say
that the vice president...

01:08:10.003 --> 01:08:14.257
Is the next in the line of succession,
but does anyone here believe...

01:08:14.424 --> 01:08:18.303
That lyndon Johnson is
the man to carry that torch?

01:08:18.845 --> 01:08:20.846
O'brien:
So, what are you suggesting?

01:08:21.014 --> 01:08:23.515
I didn't come to Washington
just to work for John Kennedy.

01:08:24.142 --> 01:08:26.978
I came here to work
for what John Kennedy believed in.

01:08:28.062 --> 01:08:29.689
There is unfinished business.

01:08:30.023 --> 01:08:33.234
Right now our only hope of completing it
is by serving his successor.

01:08:33.401 --> 01:08:35.194
Man 1:
That's not true. There are other ways.

01:08:35.361 --> 01:08:37.529
O'brien: We've come too far
to put everything on hold.

01:08:37.697 --> 01:08:41.367
So you think that Johnson will continue
the work of president Kennedy?

01:08:42.035 --> 01:08:45.912
This is a man who has fought against
every piece of civil rights legislation...

01:08:46.080 --> 01:08:48.374
For the last 20 years.

01:08:48.541 --> 01:08:50.667
How do you honor Kennedy
by working for Johnson?

01:08:50.835 --> 01:08:52.127
You're looking at it wrong.

01:08:52.295 --> 01:08:56.174
Even if Johnson believed in what
we believe in, and that is up for debate...

01:08:56.341 --> 01:08:58.421
How much do you think
he'd accomplish in one year?

01:08:58.551 --> 01:08:59.636
Man 2: Good point.

01:08:59.801 --> 01:09:01.679
Galbraith:
Could we mount a campaign by then?

01:09:01.845 --> 01:09:05.265
Salinger: Bobby is more powerful and
more popular than any other democrat...

01:09:05.433 --> 01:09:07.060
Including lyndon Johnson.

01:09:07.225 --> 01:09:10.729
The men in this room all want to see
a president, a president Kennedy...

01:09:10.897 --> 01:09:14.359
Deliver this world to a better place.
So do the people of this country.

01:09:14.524 --> 01:09:15.526
O'Donnell: Hear, hear.

01:09:15.693 --> 01:09:18.363
Sorenson: What are you
asking us to do? Quit?

01:09:18.529 --> 01:09:20.281
- Betra y lyndon Johnson?
- O'Donnell: No.

01:09:20.448 --> 01:09:22.950
No, no, no. No one is being asked
to sabotage anything.

01:09:23.117 --> 01:09:27.162
No one is calling for a mass exodus,
and this certainly is not a coup d'Ã©tat.

01:09:28.956 --> 01:09:31.501
Johnson needs to make his case
to the American people.

01:09:31.667 --> 01:09:34.252
He needs to prove
that he's worthy of this job.

01:09:34.420 --> 01:09:36.756
And if he stumbles...

01:09:38.091 --> 01:09:39.550
If he should fall...

01:09:40.968 --> 01:09:43.429
We need to be prepared
to challenge him.

01:09:44.805 --> 01:09:46.432
And it will be Bobby's time.

01:09:53.523 --> 01:09:56.150
George: We can't just sweep
the rest of the agenda under the rug.

01:09:56.317 --> 01:09:59.445
Fortas: Yes. He has to make
some progress on civil rights.

01:09:59.612 --> 01:10:02.615
George: Some. We need to be realistic.
Johnson: Howdy, Zephyr.

01:10:02.782 --> 01:10:04.617
- Evening, sir.
- Walter: Good evening, sir.

01:10:04.784 --> 01:10:07.745
Hear anything back
from the Kennedy men?

01:10:07.912 --> 01:10:10.707
Well, two nights ago,
they had a meeting...

01:10:10.873 --> 01:10:15.294
And I... I think we're gonna
hear something soon.

01:10:15.795 --> 01:10:17.964
How they going in there?

01:10:18.798 --> 01:10:20.550
It's going.

01:10:20.717 --> 01:10:23.177
Humphrey: We can't just keep doing
the same thing.

01:10:23.344 --> 01:10:26.222
George: The best thing we can do is
show some progress in civil rights.

01:10:26.389 --> 01:10:28.391
Humphrey:
"Some progress" is not enough.

01:10:28.558 --> 01:10:31.561
